  "reasonsForNoRecall": {
    "popThoughts": "We discussed these breaches via phone on 27th May at approximately 11:45am and you said you were disappointed with the issues you've been having and agreed with me that you had been doing better at the start of licence and wanted to get back to that place.",
    "licenceBreach": "You have had multiple tag breaches for your DAPOL tag, despite verbal warnings and a licence compliance letter previously being issued. Since your receipt of the licence compliance letter on 14th May 2026, there have been a further two tag breaches. These have both been battery breaches that have lasted approximately 24 hours, meaning you have not been monitored during this time. Given the serious of your domestic abuse offending history, monitoring your whereabouts and daily movements is considered essential for risk management. It is disappointing that you have not taken heed of our previous warnings and discussions and continued to breach, and for substantial amounts of time - details below.\r\n\r\n- Battery breach from 20/05/2026 at 10:56:46 until 21/05/2026 at 11:10:48. \r\nSo just before 11am last Wednesday until just after 11am the following day (Thursday last week).\r\n- Battery breach from 23/05/2026 at 06:56:01 until  24/05/2026  at 10:06:27.\r\nSo between just before 7am on Saturday (23rd May) until just after 10am on Sunday (24th May).",
    "popProgressMade": "You started off this licence period really positively, with great motivation and full compliance while you were at Glogan House Approved Premises. We have discussed with you how we have had concerns that complacency may be creeping in and you are being too relaxed with your licence conditions related to your tag and exclusion zone. This needs to change if you want to remain out of prison, which we want for you. Please take note of this final warning and make positive changes to improve your compliance because you can do very well. ",
    "noRecallRationale": "You are not being recalled at this time, however you run the risk of recall happening if you continue to have breaches like this. We want to work with you and have seen how well you can do, so we are giving you another chance to comply and show you can improve with your tag adherence. ",
    "futureExpectations": "Going forwards, you need to ensure there are no further licence breaches. Please ensure that you keep your tag charged at all times, and continuously refresh yourself of your licence conditions and requirements as we have previously discussed."
  },
  "spoRecallRationale": "Mr Hussain has received multiple battery breaches  and despite being advised to ensure his tag is charged he has continued to accrue breaches therefore  a decision has been made to issue him with a further chance to comply with this requirement via a decision not to recall letter as he is complying other wise with his licence and there are no reported concerns at this stage in relation to his risks.",
